 Phase 5: Deployment Execution (Priority 3 - Variable)

 Backend Deployment (PM2 + NGINX)

 Prerequisites:
 - Ubuntu server with Node.js 20+
 - PM2 installed globally
 - NGINX configured (use nginx.conf.template)
 - MongoDB Atlas cluster ready
 - Redis Cloud instance ready
 - SSL certificates (Let's Encrypt)

 Deployment Steps:

 # 1. Clone/pull latest code
 cd /path/to/gema/backend
 git pull origin main

 # 2. Install dependencies
 npm install --production

 # 3. Build
 npm run build

 # 4. Set environment variables
 cp .env.example .env
 nano .env  # Update with production values

 # 5. Start with PM2
 pm2 start ecosystem.config.js --env production

 # 6. Save PM2 config
 pm2 save
 pm2 startup

 # 7. Check status
 pm2 status
 pm2 logs gema-backend --lines 50

 # 8. Monitor
 pm2 monit

 NGINX Configuration:
 - Use the provided nginx.conf.template
 - SSL: Certbot for Let's Encrypt
 - Proxy: api.kidrove.com → localhost:5000
 - Rate limiting: Already configured in server.ts

 Frontend Deployment (Vercel or Netlify)

 Option A: Vercel (Recommended)

 cd frontend

 # 1. Install Vercel CLI
 npm i -g vercel

 # 2. Login
 vercel login

 # 3. Deploy
 vercel --prod

 # 4. Set environment variables in Vercel dashboard
 # Go to project settings → Environment Variables
 # Add all VITE_* variables from .env.production

 Option B: Netlify

 cd frontend

 # 1. Install Netlify CLI
 npm i -g netlify-cli

 # 2. Login
 netlify login

 # 3. Build
 npm run build

 # 4. Deploy
 netlify deploy --prod

 # 5. Set environment variables in Netlify dashboard

 Post-Deployment:
 1. Configure custom domain (kidrove.com)
 2. Verify SSL certificate auto-provisioned
 3. Test from production URL
 4. Check: API calls work, payments work, auth works

